SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 884
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to commend and congratulate Halls High School
Unified Cheerleading Team, 2025 TSSAA
Unified Cheerleading Varsity Game Day State
Champions.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school athletic teams that, through their magnificent exploits,
bring honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, the Halls High School Unified Cheerleading Team of Knoxville is one such
group of young athletes, who recently claimed the top spot in the Unified Game Day division of
competition at the 2025 TSSAA Cheer and Dance State Championships in Knoxville on
November 6-7, 2025; and
WHEREAS, after competing against four other schools, the Halls High School Unified
Cheerleading Team made history by earning the first Unified Cheerleading State Championship
title at the high school level, a most befitting honor that recognizes the team's diligence,
perseverance, and dedication to teamwork; and
WHEREAS, the members of this outstanding championship team are Isabella Glann,
Jaxson Hickman, Morgan Holbert, Obowya Lohure, Karina Naumowicz, Cassandra Popova,
Katie Quinter, Brooklyn Toney, and Jeremiah White, Hayden Evans, Natalie Hoffmeister,
Makinley Holbert, Scout Gilreath, Lydia Smith, Rylie Tollett, and Kinzlee Ferguson; and
WHEREAS, the Halls High School Unified cheerleaders were fortunate to have the
invaluable, devoted guidance of Head Coach Alex Yanniello; and
WHEREAS, displaying great sportsmanship and outstanding character throughout the
season, the members of the Halls High School Unified Cheerleading Team have conducted
themselves in a manner appropriate to the integrity of the State of Tennessee; and
SJR0884
014377
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the determination, talent, and work ethic of this group of young athletes not
only made possible a stellar triumph but also surely bode well for their future success; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the Halls High School
Unified Cheerleading Team for its outstanding performance; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we commend and honor the members of the Halls
High School Unified Cheerleading Team for their commitment to excellence, congratulate them
on being named the 2025 TSSAA Unified Cheerleading Varsity Game Day State Champions,
and extend to them our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
